Comment: 0,0:00:00.18,0:00:02.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}英文字幕
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.18,0:00:02.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hi, it's me, Tim Dodd, the Everyday Astronaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.61,0:00:07.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Remember that time when NASA sent an SUV sized rover to the surface of Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.99,0:00:13.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Yeah. You might remember the Curiosity rover and perhaps you recall its daring touchdown sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.98,0:00:16.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which utilized a rocket powered sky crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.83,0:00:20.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Whether or not you remember the Curiosity rover, I do have some great news.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.62,0:00:22.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA's about to do it again,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.35,0:00:25.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}only as you would hope they've made some awesome improvements,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}including a part of the mission that I'm super excited for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.38,0:00:32.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because they're going to be flying a drone around in the atmosphere of Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.65,0:00:37.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So in today's video, let's do an overview of this new Mars rover named Perseverance,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.29,0:00:39.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}also known as the Mars 2020 mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.65,0:00:43.50,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The rocket that'll take it to Mars, the timeline, the landing sequence,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.77,0:00:46.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then we'll compare it alongside the Curiosity rover
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.96,0:00:50.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to see what's actually changed and what stayed the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.49,0:00:53.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}including the instrumentation and the missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.58,0:00:56.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And we'll even hear from JPL engineer Bobak Ferdowsi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.74,0:01:00.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}about what he's most excited for with this awesome new Mars rover.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:02.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay. Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.01,0:01:18.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA's Curiosity rover has been a home run flagship NASA mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.72,0:01:25.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and its produced an incredible amount of data since it landed on Mars all the way back on August 6, 2012,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.55,0:01:27.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and those eight years since doing science on the surface of Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.11,0:01:30.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it found evidence of previous liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.80,0:01:34.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It discovered Mars has had the right chemistry to support living microbes,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.45,0:01:38.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}having discovered sulfur, nitrogen, oxygen, phosphorus, and carbon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.44,0:01:41.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}all the key ingredients that make life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.80,0:01:43.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}To further that note of potential life,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.85,0:01:48.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it found organic carbon molecules, active methane in the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.05,0:01:53.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and even found out that Mars once had a thicker atmosphere and more water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.32,0:01:59.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's also helped lay the foundation for future human missions to Mars by precisely measuring the radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.66,0:02:05.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}finding that Mars is radiation environment is too high for human presence, if not shielded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.61,0:02:07.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So with all this awesome stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.25,0:02:11.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}being tested and measured and discovered it raises the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.50,0:02:13.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}what else is there to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.21,0:02:17.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, what's Perseverance going to do that Curiosity didn't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.14,0:02:19.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They kind of look the same don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.20,0:02:24.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, as you can probably guess there's still a ton of science to be done
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.06,0:02:26.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and Perseverance is really going to be kicking it up a notch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.13,0:02:30.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So let's start off by doing an overview of the mission timeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:34.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then we'll go into the details of the hardware and compare those to Curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.01,0:02:39.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And since this is a pretty long video, we've got timestamps here on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.90,0:02:43.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The play bar on YouTube is actually divided into the sections.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.46,0:02:47.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And we have an article version with sources in the description as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.99,0:02:54.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance is scheduled to lift off during the 2020 launch window,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.83,0:02:57.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is from the middle of July to the middle of August.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.95,0:03:01.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}If you're watching this about August 15th, 2020,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.66,0:03:08.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it hasn't taken off, it means the next opportunity to launch isn't until August, 2022.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.69,0:03:10.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Although as of the making of this video,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.57,0:03:17.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA is looking into potentially launching a little bit after August 15th as a contingency option,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:23.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but regardless of when they actually end up launching they'll land on Mars at the exact same time and date,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.74,0:03:30.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}February 18th, 2021 at 3:30 PM Eastern, thanks to orbital mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:33.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now just like the Curiosity rover, Perseverance will be heading to Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.55,0:03:38.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}riding the Atlas 5 rocket in almost its most powerful configuration,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.38,0:03:40.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is the 541 meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.46,0:03:48.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's going to have a 5m fairing, 4 solid rocket motors and a single RL-10 centaur upper stage engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.73,0:03:54.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's going to take all that power of United launch Alliance's workhorse rocket to get the heavy Perseverance,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.13,0:03:56.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the 105 million kilometers to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.95,0:03:58.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well actually to be pedantic,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.94,0:04:05.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the distance the rover will actually travel to get to Mars is more like 497 million kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.08,0:04:08.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Because as those of you who have played Kerbal Space Program might know
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.70,0:04:13.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to get to Mars, you don't travel in a straight line when the two planets are closest to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:30.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}After its long seven month journey, Perseverance will touch down on the Martian surface in February, 2021.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.55,0:04:36.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it'll land at the Jezero crater location chosen for its possibility of harboring life in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:39.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's believed that the crater was at one point flooded with water,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:42.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which would have allowed for the presence of life in ancient times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.15,0:04:50.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The EDLS or the entry descent and landing system will contain a new technology called terrain relative navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:55.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This will allow a computer to scan the terrain during descent and then compare it to an orbital map,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:04:59.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and it will be able to divert to a safer landing zone if necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:04.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Another feature known as the range trigger will determine when the parachute should be open,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.73,0:05:08.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}allowing the rover to land much closer to points of scientific interest,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.86,0:05:15.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which ends up saving valuable time that otherwise be spent just slowly driving around on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.55,0:05:18.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So here's how that sequence of events will actually occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.82,0:05:23.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This might all sound pretty familiar if you've seen Curiosity's landing sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.22,0:05:25.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that also features the rocket powered sky-crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.83,0:05:36.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At entry minus 10 minutes, the cruise stage separates and burns up in the Martian atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.87,0:05:42.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At entry plus zero minutes, that's of course, when the craft will begin to enter the Martian atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.88,0:05:50.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Entry plus 80 seconds, the heat shield experiences, the maximum amount of heating roughly 2100 degrees Celsius.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.82,0:05:55.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At entry plus 90 seconds, the craft experiences, the maximum deceleration
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.21,0:06:05.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}slowing down from 21,200 kilometers an hour to just 1600 kilometers an hour and only two and a half minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.12,0:06:13.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At E plus 240 seconds, at an altitude of around nine to 13 kilometers, the parachute deploys.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:19.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At E plus 260 seconds shortly after, the heat shield separates and falls to the Martian surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:25.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the radar ground system will activate and begin scanning the Martian surface for a suitable touchdown zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.26,0:06:29.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At around E plus 350 seconds, the back shell separates
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.54,0:06:33.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the rover begins a brief free fall before the landing motors ignite.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.45,0:06:37.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is definitely the maximum pucker moment
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:42.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At an altitude of just 21 meters, the rover separates from the landing stage
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:46.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and is gently lowered to the ground on three nylon ropes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.03,0:06:52.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At this point, the craft has slowed down to just 2.7 kilometers an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.50,0:06:55.35,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Finally, the rover touches down on the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.41,0:07:00.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the landing stage that sky crane will fly away before it crashes into the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.91,0:07:05.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this will officially begin Perseverance its mission on the surface of Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:07.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now, if you're anything like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.36,0:07:11.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}maybe you've always wondered how can that sky crane make any sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:13.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It seems like there's a lot of extra parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:16.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}extra systems dangling from this rope and all this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.93,0:07:19.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It seems like a lot more trouble than it's worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:25.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Why don't they just put the rover on top of the sky-crane and just land it like normal and drive off the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.15,0:07:28.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Wouldn't that be a lot it's easier and lighter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.84,0:07:31.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, to answer that there's really two main reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.61,0:07:35.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the first one is, when you have something as heavy as Perseverance,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.59,0:07:38.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is about a metric ton landing propulsively
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.78,0:07:42.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you can't have the rocket engines firing too close to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.97,0:07:45.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You'll basically make a crater, which is the same reason
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.89,0:07:52.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}why we're seeing the lunar Lander version of Starship have auxiliary landing engines up really high.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.66,0:07:55.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So if you did put the rover on top of it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.08,0:07:57.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and you wanted to make sure those rockets weren't too close to the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.89,0:08:01.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}you'd have to put it on like giant stilts or giant landing legs and those weigh a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.49,0:08:05.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And then now your rover's on top of a giant thing with landing legs and stilts,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.10,0:08:10.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and to drive it off, you'd have to have this ramp or some kind of system then to get it off of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:15.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And now you just added even more weight and complexity and made it pretty, pretty risky, honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.97,0:08:17.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the other reason is actually for control.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.35,0:08:22.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a lot easier to let the crane just kind of hover roughly above the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.09,0:08:25.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then use a tether that has some slack in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:27.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So there's a lot of wiggle room there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.97,0:08:30.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You basically to start lowering the rover until it touches the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.64,0:08:31.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Once it touches the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.63,0:08:34.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they cut those tethers and the sky crane just flies away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.96,0:08:38.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it doesn't need to get down perfectly and just land very, very, very gently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:45.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So again, this all sounds like deja vu with Curiosity having done quite literally all of this stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.14,0:08:49.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}proving out this entire system and all the wacky landing sequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:55.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So let's actually compare these two rovers side-by-side and then we'll see what's new and note-worthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.47,0:09:01.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, to begin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.10,0:09:08.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}both rovers are virtually identical designs with Perseverance actually using some of Curiosity's backup parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.57,0:09:15.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Each rover is 2.9 meters wide, 2.7 meters long, and 2.2 meters tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:20.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's easy to forget just how big these rovers are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:22.91,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, they're almost the size of a small SUV.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.33,0:09:25.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Although they're nearly identical in size,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:33.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance will be heavier, weighing in at 1050 kilograms versus Curiosity's 899 kilograms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.44,0:09:37.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So let's take a look at the changes that make Perseverance heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.04,0:09:39.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Both rovers utilize the same body,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.27,0:09:43.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is called the WEB or the warm electronics box.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.83,0:09:48.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's this strong outer layer that protects the computers and the electronics
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.39,0:09:50.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and keeps them temperature controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.66,0:09:55.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}On top of the web or the deck is the large mast that houses the main cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.67,0:09:58.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which are the super cam and the Mast Cam Z.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.85,0:10:04.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then there's the Mars environmental dynamic analyzer or known as MEDA,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.13,0:10:06.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is basically a little weather station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:10.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And on the bottom of Perseverance is a sample collecting system.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:14.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this is one of the biggest upgrades for Perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.64,0:10:17.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance will collect rock cores for future study.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.53,0:10:22.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this is a little confusing to me because the samples will just be stored,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:28.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}ready for someone or something else to pick them up and return them for further analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.96,0:10:31.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But if something else comes along to grab these samples,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.01,0:10:35.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}why can't that thing just drill its own core samples?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.19,0:10:38.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Isn't that kind of trivial compared to getting to Mars?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.51,0:10:42.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, isn't it actually kind of hard to have to retrace Perseverance's steps
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.97,0:10:47.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and grab all of its cores instead of just drilling its own samples itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.78,0:10:55.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Well, first off storing samples before any more human interference or future Mars missions land on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.58,0:10:59.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}ensures clean samples before any potential contamination.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.05,0:11:05.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So that's a good thing, but second, it also saves the weight of the heavy drill and containment system
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.27,0:11:08.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}from being required on a future rover.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.88,0:11:11.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance, will collect at least 20 samples.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.14,0:11:17.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It has 43 sample collecting containers and five witness tubes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.27,0:11:21.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So what they're going to do is they'll open up these witness tubes during drilling sessions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.08,0:11:26.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that are preloaded with materials that can capture molecular and particle contaminants.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.63,0:11:32.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In other words, these witness tubes will capture gases that may be released or out gas from the rover itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.87,0:11:35.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}chemical remanence from the landing system
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.85,0:11:42.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or any other earthly organic or inorganic material that may have somehow made its way to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.23,0:11:45.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This ensures that there's a control to observe later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.65,0:11:47.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So when they're looking at samples,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.30,0:11:49.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they can cross reference the witness tubes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.95,0:11:55.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that'll let them know whether or not the materials actually from the sample or from the rover,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:57.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or potentially even from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.80,0:12:01.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The rover stores the tubes under its belly on a carousel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.49,0:12:05.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And there's a small robot arm that hands, the sample tubes off to the main arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.83,0:12:10.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's kind of like a lab assistant to the big arm, which is kind of cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.74,0:12:13.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then depending on what NASA ends up wanting to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.70,0:12:16.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it'll do a deposit of the samples all at once
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:20.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or in a few strategic places for future sample collection and return.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.37,0:12:25.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's even already plans in the works with ESA and NASA to send another rover down
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.03,0:12:29.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that will have a mini rocket on it, and basically be a small launch pad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.07,0:12:34.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And that's of course possible because Mars has a lot lower gravity as my shirt will tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.85,0:12:38.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and a lower atmosphere, which shirt will also tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.54,0:12:43.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So it takes a lot smaller rocket to get something from Mars into Mars orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.74,0:12:46.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then back to Earth than it would to get something from Earth to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.91,0:12:50.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay. So they'll take this new rover, drive it over to a sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.80,0:12:55.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They'll stick that sample on this little rocket they'll launch that rocket into Mars orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.43,0:13:00.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and then it will likely rendezvous with another probe that will end up pushing it all the way to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.58,0:13:05.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now these plans change and they won't happen until at least 2028.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:10.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So we won't be getting any sense sample returns until the 2030s at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.13,0:13:16.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this feels like a pretty hail Mary stretch of events to have to work perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.89,0:13:20.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It almost makes me wonder if humans will just end up collecting those samples themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.49,0:13:26.39,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or just bringing their own drills and observing Mars right there on a Martian base or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.40,0:13:28.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or bringing them back to earth with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.44,0:13:31.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But although it's definitely a cool way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.09,0:13:35.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and an important thing to preserve samples before any human presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:38.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay so back to Perseverance and that big arm on the front,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.84,0:13:41.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it's been massively upgraded compared to Curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:46.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It has a new hand or a turret full of new science tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:52.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It also has an updated coring drill and two science instruments alongside a color camera
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.44,0:13:57.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}for closeups surface inspections and those awesome selfies like Curiosity has taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:14:00.48,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Learning from the issues with Curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:03.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the teams at NASA have made some significant changes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.73,0:14:08.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that should extend the rover's lifespan and allow it to conduct even more science.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.76,0:14:13.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The biggest change is probably the wheels which have been redesigned to have a larger diameter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.96,0:14:17.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and a smaller tread width than Curiosity's wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.31,0:14:23.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}These new wheels should prevent Perseverance from getting stuck in the Martian sand, as Curiosity did in 2014.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.91,0:14:30.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance also has a new cutting edge instrument suite using its x-ray spectrometer and UV laser.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:37.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It'll scan the Martian surface at an even finer scale than ever before, to search for evidence of Martian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.20,0:14:43.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perhaps one of the upgrades that I'm most excited for is its huge upgrade to cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.53,0:14:48.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance will carry a remarkable 23 cameras to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.78,0:14:54.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Including some that will film the final descent the Martian atmosphere, capturing all inspiring footage,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.59,0:14:57.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}as the craft drifts down towards the Martian surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.77,0:15:00.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The new cameras will also be higher resolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.72,0:15:05.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}While Curiosity's best camera was only about two megapixels.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.02,0:15:10.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The camera on board will capture 20 megapixel full color images.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.48,0:15:14.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now I know that this might not seem like the most scientifically valuable thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.31,0:15:17.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but I think it's one of the most important pieces of the mission
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.88,0:15:23.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that help raise the public's interest and help all of us get a sense of actually being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.81,0:15:27.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}After all, Public interest is a big part of these flagship NASA missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.91,0:15:32.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this has a few fun elements that you may have actually been a part of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.68,0:15:39.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance will be carrying 10.9 million names on board, three thumbnail sized Silicon chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.77,0:15:40.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Maybe your name's on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.44,0:15:47.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's also a tribute plate to the medical community and another with an image of earth Mars and the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.25,0:15:51.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And the rover was named Perseverance by Alex Mather
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.52,0:15:57.05,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}who won a  K-12 public naming contest with 28,000 entries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.40,0:16:00.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I love seeing the public gets so involved in these missions,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.55,0:16:06.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but to expand on the public experience, Perseverance will also carry two microphones,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.40,0:16:12.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which will capture the sound of Mars during the landing as well as on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.21,0:16:14.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I can't wait for all the footage to roll in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.65,0:16:20.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Beautiful descent footage with real sound, awesome high resolution images.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.51,0:16:24.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, Perseverance would be bringing Mars to us better than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.25,0:16:28.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance's power system will basically be the same thing as Curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:31.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which has proven to be incredibly reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.66,0:16:37.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's a 45 kilogram radioisotopic thermal electric generator or an RTG
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:43.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that converts the heat of radioactive decay of plutonium into electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.26,0:16:49.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Along with the RTG, there's also pair of lithium ion batteries to help handle peak demands
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.31,0:16:53.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or times when the rover is using more energy than the RTG produces.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.69,0:16:56.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The RTG is designed to last 14 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.05,0:17:03.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is fine beyond the plan mission duration of 1.5 Mars years or three earth years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.49,0:17:07.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is a pretty typical JPL thing to over-engineer
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.08,0:17:12.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and we're definitely thankful when it comes to rovers like Curiosity and Perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:18.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I guess, Opportunity also who have exceeded all expectations of life duration.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.40,0:17:21.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I mean, they just keep on going!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.71,0:17:23.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Fun side note here about the RTG.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.65,0:17:27.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This will be the first mission to launch from the US utilizing an RTG
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.03,0:17:32.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that won't require the president to directly approve the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.59,0:17:36.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The permissions have changed allowing NASA administrators to approve the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.21,0:17:41.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So our good friend, Jim Bridenstine will give his thumbs up and it'll be launch time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.22,0:17:47.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Another thing that's just like Curiosity, Perseverance, will use three forms of communications.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.59,0:17:53.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}An ultra high frequency antenna with data transmission of up to two megabits per second,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.49,0:17:55.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}from the rover to the relay link.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.35,0:17:57.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Then there's the X-band high gain antenna,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.75,0:18:05.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which has a steerable beam that can transmit data directly to earth at 160 to 500 bits per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.76,0:18:09.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And lastly, there's an X band, low gain antenna,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.54,0:18:14.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is primarily for receiving signals and can only transfer 10 bits per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.36,0:18:19.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So you really don't want to use this for any images or anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.55,0:18:22.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Another fun upgrade and experiment that's going to be on Perseverance,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.22,0:18:27.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and something that's going to be really useful for future crewed missions to Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.34,0:18:32.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}will be the first attempts at producing oxygen on the surface of Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.68,0:18:38.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}using in-situ resource utilization with an awesome experiment called MOXIE.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.78,0:18:44.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Although Mars has an atmosphere, it's very thin as you can read on my shirt here again,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.18,0:18:47.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}only about 1% as dense as Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:55.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and of that 1% density, carbon dioxide makes up around 96% of the gas in Mars' atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.75,0:19:04.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Oxygen is only 0.174% compared to the 21% in Earth's much thicker atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.25,0:19:09.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Getting really pedantic here if you factor in the partial pressures of earth and Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.92,0:19:13.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}take the average temperature into consideration and convert to moles,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.25,0:19:25.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}taking a breath on Mars, you'd only inhale about 0.0071% as much oxygen as you would at sea level on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.01,0:19:34.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Or in other words, there's about 14,000 times more oxygen per liter on Earth than on the surface of Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.36,0:19:39.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So if humans are going to live on Mars, we've got to make oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.81,0:19:44.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And maybe just as importantly, if these humans are to return home,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:46.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they'll need oxygen for their rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:53.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So figuring out how to make oxygen out of the carbon dioxide in the atmosphere of Mars is vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.41,0:19:57.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And as if all of this wasn't just enough, awesome upgrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.66,0:20:04.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance has one more incredible trick up its sleeve, or should I say under its belly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.68,0:20:07.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perseverance will not be flying alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.60,0:20:12.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It'll be joined by a small drone helicopter named Ingenuity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.00,0:20:16.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Ingenuity will demonstrate the possibility of flight on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.62,0:20:21.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and will provide engineers on Earth with aerial images to better plan routes for Perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.10,0:20:23.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Because of its proximity to the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.24,0:20:29.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Ingenuity will capture images with approximately 10 times the resolution of orbital images.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.99,0:20:31.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Ingenuity is pretty lightweight though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:38.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It only weighs 1.8 kilograms and has two counter-rotating rotors that are 120 centimeters in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.12,0:20:39.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It's pretty awesome
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.79,0:20:44.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that they can just use to counter-rotating blades to be able to do all the control dynamics of this vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.18,0:20:50.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The little helicopter drone is expected to fly at least five times in its 30 day test campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.87,0:20:54.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with each flight lasting no more than just three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.52,0:20:58.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}While that's not that long of times, of course
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.04,0:21:01.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the blades have to do quite a bit of work in that really thin atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.42,0:21:02.95,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The idea of there being a drone,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.95,0:21:06.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that's just flying around on another planet though, millions of kilometers away,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.76,0:21:09.70,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}honestly, absolutely incredible to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.00,0:21:13.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Okay. Okay. Okay. I might just be a little bit biased.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.33,0:21:18.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Perhaps I just think it's extra cool because I've seen it with my own eyes from only a few meters away
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.15,0:21:21.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}while it was going through its final testing at JPL.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.05,0:21:26.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this will just be the first of hopefully many drones to fly around on other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.67,0:21:29.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Because of course, I'm also looking forward to the dragonfly mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.30,0:21:35.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it'll be a quad copter that'll be flying around on Saturn's largest moon Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.84,0:21:39.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but that won't happen until the mid 2030s.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.03,0:21:46.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So Perseverance is a pretty massive overhaul of Curiosity and has a ton of cool things to look forward to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.45,0:21:52.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So all this said, I asked my friend and JPL engineer Bobak Ferdowsi what he was most excited for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.95,0:21:57.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hey Tim, it's Bobak, you know, as one of the people who got to work on Curiosity and help get it to Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.86,0:22:00.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with Perseverance kind of being like a 2.0 version of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.03,0:22:03.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It feels a little bit like a proud grandparent now,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.81,0:22:06.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and I'm really excited for the mission and what it's going to accomplish
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.47,0:22:08.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and all the improvements that were made from Curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.61,0:22:12.26,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I think two that stand out to me in particular: Terrain relative navigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.36,0:22:16.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that's basically where the rover can avoid major obstacles during the landing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.17,0:22:18.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that really increases the chance of landing safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.69,0:22:22.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I would say the MOXIE instrument where it's creating oxygen on the atmosphere of Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.75,0:22:26.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}not only does that mean incredible things for generating fuel on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.45,0:22:30.43,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but as somebody who kind of hopes one day maybe to visit their baby on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.69,0:22:32.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I would love to have lost the oxygen when I get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.97,0:22:34.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm really excited for the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.23,0:22:36.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I wish them all a super safe and successful journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.81,0:22:38.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I can't wait to see what this mission shows us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.52,0:22:43.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Personally, I think I'm in between Ingenuity the drone and just seeing better images in general,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.43,0:22:46.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but then again, In-Situ resource utilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.88,0:22:48.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}That's going to be amazing. I mean, think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.87,0:22:54.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX's Starship will require In-Situ resource utilization in order to get back from Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.75,0:22:56.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It has to make its own fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.51,0:22:58.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It has to make methane and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.76,0:23:01.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So I mean, it's a vital thing that needs to be tested out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.90,0:23:05.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's just so many awesome things to look forward to on Perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.57,0:23:09.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I don't know if I can pick a favorite, but what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.38,0:23:11.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}What are you most looking forward to?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.51,0:23:14.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}What other questions do you have about this mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.19,0:23:17.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Maybe you're one of the people has their name on Perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.76,0:23:20.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Let me know your thoughts or questions in the comments below.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.70,0:23:24.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But if you have any more questions, you can join me live for this launch,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.06,0:23:26.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}whenever that happens and the landing,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.40,0:23:28.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}both of which I will live stream with you all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.79,0:23:33.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and help point out all of the exciting things along the way and answer your questions live.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.54,0:23:37.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Thank you guys for hanging out with me and my brand new studio space that I'm still working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.57,0:23:39.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's still a lot more work to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.36,0:23:42.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}You'll probably be seeing some different changes in different backgrounds in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.90,0:23:44.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm still working on quite a bit of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.67,0:23:50.27,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I owe of that to my Patreon supporters for helping me make all of this stuff possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.27,0:23:51.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Making hardware upgrades,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.89,0:23:56.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}hopefully better image quality we're shooting in 6k now everybody! I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.09,0:23:58.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I'm just so thankful to be able to take this little,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.52,0:24:02.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}little hobby of mine and turn it into a career. Thank you to you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.03,0:24:04.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So if you want to help me continue to do what I do
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.36,0:24:07.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or get your thoughts and comments on videos before they come out,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.34,0:24:10.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}maybe you want to talk in our exclusive discord channel
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.18,0:24:13.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or join our subreddit or gain access to our exclusive live streams,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.58,0:24:19.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}head on over to patreon.com/everyday. Astronaut. Thank you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.16,0:24:19.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And while you're online,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.88,0:24:22.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}be sure and check out my web store for new shirts like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.97,0:24:26.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The awesome future Martian society shirt,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.09,0:24:29.23,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which as mentioned has Mars is atmospheric composition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.23,0:24:32.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and gravity and reminder to wear a space suit if you're outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.90,0:24:37.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But it also has the exact landing coordinates of Starship at its prime A
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.73,0:24:41.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}candidate landing site on Arcadia Planatia, Elon Musk even noticed when I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.87,0:24:44.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I was wearing a shirt and last time I interviewed him and he goes, "Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.51,0:24:47.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Arcadia Planatia, is that your favorite place on Mars? I go,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.60,0:24:51.47,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}"I think it is, but really it's your favorite place!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.47,0:24:57.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Because this is the prime candidate landing site for Starship" and he just laughed. He's like, "yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.02,0:25:02.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that's awesome." So you can get your own awesome shirt or other cool merchandise,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.12,0:25:04.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}by going to everydayastronaut.com/shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.64,0:25:07.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And I owe a special thanks to Caspar Stanley from Stanley creative,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.82,0:25:11.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}for his help, with the 3D animations and 3D renders in this video,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.81,0:25:14.54,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}check out his awesome Rocket Explorer app,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.54,0:25:19.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or maybe show him some love by supporting his awesome work on Patreon too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.16,0:25:22.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And perhaps you noticed my MOVA globe here on the desk or in the background,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.04,0:25:25.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I've had these MOVA Globes for years they're some of my favorite things ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.03,0:25:28.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They're just powered by light. There's no batteries or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.40,0:25:30.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There's a link in the description on where you can get your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.77,0:25:32.93,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I promise if you get one and you have it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.93,0:25:36.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}every guest that's over is going to be like, how does that work?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.68,0:25:39.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They're just going to be mesmerized. They're absolutely incredible. So again,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.98,0:25:42.14,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}check the link in the description below to see how you can get yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.66,0:25:44.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Thanks everybody, that's going to do it for me.
